subject:

HATRED AND MURDER: THE ONLY CURE
===================================================================
verse:

Love does no harm to its neighbor. Therefore love is The
fulfillment of the law. (Ro. 13:10) - (read Ro. 13:8-14)

===================================================================
reflection:

Killing is an old sin. Remember the story of Cain and Abel?
Cain killed his brother out of jealousy. There is only one
way to overcome hatred and what it can lead to, and that is
to become a new person in Christ, to be clothed with Him and
to have Him in your heart by faith in His saving merit.
Faith gives way to love for the neighbor, even for one who
sins against us. In I Cor. 13:7 Paul declared that love
“always protects, always trusts, always hopes, always
perseveres.” The next time we make a claim about our love
let us remember Paul’s definition of love.

===================================================================
prayer:

Lord Jesus, transform our hearts so that hatred gives way to
Your love. Clothe us in Your grace that we may forgive those
who sin against us and reflect Your love even to our
enemies. Teach us to love with patience, hope, and
perseverance, following the example of Paul's description of
true love. Help us to be instruments of Your peace and
healing in a world torn by conflict. Amen. (AI)

===================================================================
